  "faq_title": "FAQ",
  "faq_categoryGeneral": "General",
  "faq_categoryUsage": "How to Use",
  "faq_categoryAccount": "Account",
  "faq_categoryPet": "Pet Management",
  "faq_q1": "Is this app free?",
  "faq_a1": "Basic features of Perch Care are free. Subscribe to Premium for additional features like AI Vision Health Check.",
  "faq_q2": "How accurate is the AI health analysis?",
  "faq_a2": "AI analysis is for reference only and does not replace professional diagnosis. If your pet has health concerns, please consult a veterinarian.",
  "faq_q3": "Is my data stored safely?",
  "faq_a3": "All data is encrypted and securely stored on our servers. Your data is restored when you log in on a new device.",
  "faq_q4": "How do I record weight?",
  "faq_a4": "Go to the Weight tab in the bottom navigation, select a date, and enter the weight in grams.",
  "faq_q5": "How do I record food and water?",
  "faq_a5": "Tap the food or water card on the Home screen to go to the recording page. Add items and save.",
  "faq_q6": "What is BHI (Health Index)?",
  "faq_a6": "BHI (Bird Health Index) is a score that combines weight, food, and water records to show your bird's overall health status.",
  "faq_q7": "Can I edit or delete records?",
  "faq_a7": "Yes, tap a food record to edit it. Swipe left on an item to delete it.",
  "faq_q8": "How do I change the language?",
  "faq_a8": "Go to Profile > Language Settings and choose between Korean, English, or Chinese.",
  "faq_q9": "How do I link or unlink social accounts?",
  "faq_a9": "Go to Profile > Social Account Linking to manage Google and Apple account connections.",
  "faq_q10": "What happens to my data if I delete my account?",
  "faq_a10": "All personal information and pet records are permanently deleted and cannot be recovered.",
  "faq_q11": "How do I add or delete a pet?",
  "faq_a11": "Go to Profile > My Pets. Use the (+) button to add and the (X) button to delete.",
  "faq_q12": "Which species are supported?",
  "faq_a12": "Currently parrots (budgies, cockatiels, etc.) are supported. Other bird species will be added in the future.",
  "faq_q13": "Is Android or HarmonyOS supported?",
  "faq_a13": "Currently only iOS is supported. Android and HarmonyOS versions are in development and will be released in the future.",
  "faq_categoryPremium": "Premium",
  "faq_q14": "What is Premium?",
  "faq_a14": "Premium provides advanced features including unlimited AI Vision Health Check and image-based detailed analysis.",
  "faq_q15": "How do I use a Premium code?",
  "faq_a15": "Go to Profile > Premium and enter your code in the format PERCH-XXXX-XXXX to activate immediately.",
  "faq_q16": "What happens to my data when Premium expires?",
  "faq_a16": "Your health check text results are retained after expiration. However, health check images are automatically deleted from the server 90 days after expiration.",
  "faq_q17": "How do I use AI Vision Health Check?",
  "faq_a17": "Tap the 'AI Health Check' button on the Home screen, select an analysis type (full body/body part/droppings/food), then take a photo or choose from your album.",
  "faq_q18": "Which body parts can be analyzed?",
  "faq_a18": "You can analyze full body, eyes, beak, feathers, and feet individually. Droppings analysis and food safety checks are also available.",
  "faq_q19": "Where can I view health check records?",
